Others: Zack Wheeler pitched a dominant game against the Atlanta Braves, extending the Phillies' National League East lead to six games.
Wheeler has a 2.38 ERA since June 22 and a 1.61 ERA in August.
Wheeler is in the National League Cy Young Award race, with a 2.63 ERA and 183 strikeouts.
Chris Sale is the favorite for the Cy Young Award, but Wheeler has a better WHIP.
Wheeler has a 2.07 ERA in 104 1/3 innings against Atlanta since joining the Phillies in 2020.
